Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.74,0:01:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico be behind me. Say hi to everybody.\NOh, honey, sweetheart. You meet people who look
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.99,0:01:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar. I don't know, they look familiar? Hi.\NI get to walk through the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.63,0:01:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on my hands, with my hands.\NGood to see you. Anybody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.10,0:01:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to shake his hand?\NFrom bigism to longism.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.90,0:02:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.14,0:02:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. The long arm.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.63,0:02:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I shake your hand? I didn't know.\NSome of the old regulars. There's all the regulars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.63,0:02:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOne more.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.65,0:02:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she got two.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.31,0:03:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody I'm missing?\NIt's so good to see you. Ah, look who's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.66,0:03:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you're looking great today. This is a fancy\Nlooking jacket. Hi, sweetheart. I've seen you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi. Did I shake everybody's hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't. Almost.\NWe're going to leave a little more time for questions and answers, because we always get
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.38,0:03:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of jammed up at the end of the day. So I'll lecture less in the afternoon,\Nbut get more time. And maybe next year we'll spend more and more time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.58,0:04:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with, you know, interviews and discussions.\NAll right. I start all the books and end all the books
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.04,0:04:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with Gloria and Excelsis Deo.\NIf that fries you, you're reading the wrong book.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I put that on as\Na protection at the front of the book. You know, the book
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.74,0:04:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,versus falsehood. I expected a rain of complaints, and there practically has been\Nnone, because the people I don't want to read it can't get past
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.74,0:04:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that page. See, I warn everybody,\Nit starts and it ends with Gloria and Excelsis Deo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.62,0:04:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To thee, O Lord, we acknowledge.\NWe acknowledge thee, O Lord, as sovereign.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.51,0:05:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The narcissistic ego has a difficult\Ntime acknowledging that God is sovereign and it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't.\NThe human race has lamented that for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so I just thought we'd mention that. Next year\Nwe'll do six Alder Hutchers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.29,0:05:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of twelve like we did this year, or ten, whatever it was.\NBut we'll spend more time with discussion, because we've
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.22,0:05:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much gone over a lot of the academic material. And in the\Nintervening months, I thought we'd do something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll produce like a, what do you call those things you play in your car\Nwhen you're driving? A CD? Is that it? CD?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.76,0:05:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A CD disc, you know. So I thought we'd do them every other\Nmonth, so you can have something at home. You don't have to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.79,0:06:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDo more of those things that you can have at your own convenience
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.06,0:06:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,without having to travel and go to the\Nexpense of all that. So we'll try that. And Robert,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.22,0:06:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the man in the wall, is building a\Nwe're going to have our own recording studio at home, so we'll be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.22,0:06:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I always like President Roosevelt's fireside chats, you know.\NSort of a fireside chat. Where you really talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, what you've been talking about.\NOn a one-to-one basis, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.61,0:06:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, how many people here are new this time? New?\NOh my, we have. Yes, okay. So we always have
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.70,0:06:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the new and the regulars. So because of the new,\NI recapitulate the basics of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.80,0:07:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness research. The basic\Ndiscovery of consciousness research is so mind-boggling
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that few are the people on the planet that can comprehend it.\NThe only criticisms we've
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.86,0:07:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,ever gotten about the work were from people who were completely unable to comprehend it.\NWe never got a single complaint that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.86,0:07:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated over 200. Can you imagine that with all the books and all the videos and all the lectures?\NNot one single complaint could calibrate over 200, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.86,0:07:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It is mind-boggling.\NFor the first time in all of human evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.23,0:07:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there is now the capacity to discern truth from falsehood.\NThat is so mind-boggling that very few
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.62,0:08:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,people really comprehend it. The capacity to discern\Ntruth from falsehood is mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.02,0:08:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's limited to people who are aligned with truth rather than\Nfalsehood. So only people who calibrate over 200 can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.53,0:08:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology is so simple. It's a\Nphysiologic response, a physiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between truth and falsehood, somehow\Nunconsciously we always know it. There are many physiologic changes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.78,0:08:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,other than the kinesiologic response. The kinesiologic\Nresponse is just very, very handy. It's quick and handy. You know, it takes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,about this long once you know how to do it. There's other physiologic\Nchanges. In fact, Brock gave me one off the internet
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.03,0:08:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,yesterday, that your gastric motility changes when you\Nlie. And they say it's even better than a lie detector.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.19,0:09:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nisn't that true? I don't know where Brock escaped to, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives me these mind-boggling things and then he twists out the door before I ask him\Nquestions about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.54,0:09:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so there are many physiologic\Nchanges having to do with the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,intuitively we understand\Nthat we detect that there is a difference between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.77,0:09:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The kinesiologic response is just good\Nfor research. There's many other reflexes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.77,0:09:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember crossing over into Northern Ireland\Nat a time when there was war between Northern Ireland, the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.80,0:09:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Protestants and the Catholics or whatever it was.\NWhen you crossed the border, they patted you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.50,0:09:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And as they patted you down, they looked intently into your eyes and asked you\Nare you carrying any weapons? Do you intend any violence?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.73,0:10:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And they watched your pupil response.\NI said to it after I was through it, I said to one of the detectives,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.05,0:10:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,why do you ask that? I got it. The pupil response\Nis immediate. The breathing changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brain electroencephalograph changes. There are a whole\Nthere's endocrine changes. There's a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.90,0:10:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote about them someplace.\NAnyway, Brock brought in a new one I thought you needed to know about. It affects
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.90,0:10:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,your gastric motility as well. In fact, the article, the research\Nrecommends that the gastric motility response is probably more reliable
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.10,0:10:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,than the traditional lie detector tests. Blood pressure,\Nperspiration, all the various things. But
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.26,0:10:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology is quick and easy and therefore\Nto those people who can't understand it, you don't need to understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.58,0:11:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You just need to do it and it works. That's all it says.\NThings that are very simple mystify people. Things that are complicated, everybody gets sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.61,0:11:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NI was going to bring a couple pictures from home this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.56,0:11:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, just to demonstrate. Maybe we'll do it at the next lecture.\NHow quickly, intuitively, it discerns
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.56,0:11:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood, the real from the fake, the forgery from the original.\NAlright, so I'll just recapitulate again how this all arose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a huge clinic back east.\NThe largest psychiatric practice in the United States. 2,000 outpatients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.36,0:11:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,1,000 new patients a year.\NI had a staff of 50 people, covered a couple floors, all kinds of laboratories
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and diagnostic things. 10-channel grass electroencephalogram.\NWe did 5-hour glucose tolerance tests and we did the electroencephalogram
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.58,0:11:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,every half hour. Because so many things\Nwere incurable. One of the reasons things were incurable
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.65,0:12:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the difference between academic and clinical science.\NSee, clinical science deals with what is. Academic science deals with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.65,0:12:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,what it thinks is.\NSo, in those days, people were
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.90,0:12:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,coming in by the droll.\NBecause they'd been everywhere in the world and hadn't been cured, otherwise they wouldn't be coming to the clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.90,0:12:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we had all the difficult cases from all over the world.\NThey'd seen all the world's experts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.38,0:12:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we used every holistic health. Everything that academic science\Ntended to poo-poo was unproven. But clinical science found useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.38,0:12:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because clinically, as a physician, I can remember\Nlooking at this patient in my office, and I knew what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,non-academic therapeutic method would probably bring about recovery.\NAnd I had to make a decision. Was I going to please my colleagues
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.47,0:13:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the medical establishment, or was my obligation to this patient?\NMy obligation is to God. And at the moment of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.63,0:13:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be accountable for what I did for him.\NYou're not going to win a popularity contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.98,0:13:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, I practiced sort of non-traditional, holistic, before it was\Nfashionable, holistic medicine. And we did,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.62,0:13:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as I say, all these tests. People poo-pooed hypoglycemia.\NAnd so we did 5-hour glucose tolerance tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.62,0:13:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd give you a huge dose of glucose, and then chart your blood sugar\Nover a period of time. And, of course, you see a normal person
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.82,0:13:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who goes up like this, and comes down slowly. Well, some people have a\Nhyperinsulin response. You give them sugar, and it goes up like this, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.82,0:13:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it rockets down below normal. And as it rockets down\Nbelow normal, they begin to shake. Some people become violent. Some people
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.82,0:14:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,become psychotic. Some people become irrational. And I told you\Nabout the lady during the glucose tolerance test, who tore off all her
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.94,0:14:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,clothes and ran down the street.\NPeople poo-pooed hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.94,0:14:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When her blood sugar got down to about 70,\Nshe got quite psychotic, and voices told her to take off her clothes, which she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.94,0:14:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And she ran down the sidewalk. And the big lab director\Nwith his long white coat running after her, come back, Ms. Swanson, come back, Ms. Swanson,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.14,0:14:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the traffic all going crazy on the road.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.81,0:14:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply stopping sugar and sweets cures a lot of illnesses. Depression,\Nand rage attacks, and recovery from addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.81,0:14:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and alcohol, and various things. Anyway, so I was\Nopen to anything that might be helpful. We checked out things like
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.81,0:14:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,cerebral allergy, which was also poo-pooed, and\Nvery dilute solution. You hold it on the tongue, and a very dilute solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.26,0:15:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people become psychotic and irrational right at that moment.\NThe most intractable, difficult case I had, a chronic paranoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And we tested him with, I remember, potato, 1 to 100,000 or something.\NAnd the minute it was put on the tongue, he instantly became psychotic and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.12,0:15:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,delusional and potentially violent. So we put down\Nin his hospital chart, do not allow potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.12,0:15:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no clinical proof, you know,\Nscientific proof. If you're going to wait around for proof of things, you're going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.25,0:15:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,long dead, because the proof of any of the simplest things in life,\Nyou know, took many decades. So I heard about
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.28,0:15:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology. It was another way to help people. And I think I've told this story\Nbefore, but I went to the lecture by John
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Diamond. He's an excellent teacher, and he wrote a couple of good books.\NIt's very clear. And when I
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.38,0:16:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,saw people go weak with certain things, I just\Nsaw it from a different dimension. So I saw its usefulness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.89,0:16:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in clinical science. You know, if I want to give myself\Na medication, you know how I figure out the dose. I say, this was
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.89,0:16:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,50 milligrams, 100 milligrams, 150, so I take 150.\NAnd as a result, my thyroid function is normal,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.27,0:16:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,having figured out the dose of kinesiology. So,\Nanyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.75,0:16:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw this from a different dimension, because I'd had some other staggering\Nspiritual experiences very young in life. And I saw it as a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.75,0:16:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,holistic, I saw it as a total response of consciousness.\NSo I wanted to show the staff how we could use this. So I would go
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.42,0:16:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,all over the world and learn these various holistic techniques, and then I'd bring it home.\NBack to the clinic, staff get together, and I'd give them a lecture of what I'd learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.42,0:17:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'd all try it and see whether, you know, as long as it's harmless,\Nwhether it would be helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.42,0:17:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, it made the University\Nsuccess and failure in a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.42,0:17:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,huge number of cases. Otherwise, we wouldn't have had\Nthe largest psychiatric practice in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So...\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.90,0:17:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so I was going to show it to the\Nstaff. Alright, we had
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.90,0:17:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the Attitude and the Healing\NCenter, which of course are Miracle students.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.90,0:17:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And so\NI grabbed a couple of them, and I said
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.97,0:17:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,come over here. And, you know,\Nwith fluorescent lights, everybody will go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.97,0:17:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take the average person, have a look at the\Nand go like this, they go weak. If you hold pesticides, or we used to use sweet and low,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they go weak. All right, well, these people didn't go weak. What's the matter with them?\NEverybody goes weak except them. And I found they were advanced students of A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.47,0:18:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we began testing their response. So we started with some new students of A Course in\NMiracles, and we started and tested them every week, or a couple times a month anyway. We said,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.65,0:18:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the fluorescent lights, they go weak. And put something, we wouldn't even tell them what it\Nis. Susan and I demonstrated this a few lectures ago, pesticides made you go weak. And then we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.86,0:18:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered that at about lectures, at about less than 75 or 80, around in there, in A Course in\NMiracles, some shift of consciousness occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And now they could look at a fluorescent light, and they would not go weak. In other words, they've\Ngotten the concept that you're only, you're an infinite being, and you're only subject to what you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.42,0:18:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,hold in mind. You're only subject to what you hold in mind. You're not subject to out there-ness,\Nyou're only subject to in here-ness, a rather enormous jump in level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.52,0:18:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the basis then of the discovery. And then the calibrations all occurred later.\NSo we can start with the first slide, which, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.46,0:19:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody has seen many times. But we're not going to spend a great deal of time on it.\NThere was a series of lectures I did do, and spent a great deal of time on it. And now they're being
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.04,0:19:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,transcribed, transcribed, a lot of time on each level. In the book that's going to be out, I guess,\Nby the time of the next lecture, called Transcending Levels of Consciousness, we go into each of these
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.96,0:19:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness.\NIt has to do with how to. You know, what is the block at this level? What's holding you back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.39,0:19:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the payoff that you're attached to? So you're not attached to grief, anger, self-pity, and all those\Nthings. You think you are. Or materialism, or sexual compulsions, et cetera. You're not attached to those
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.89,0:20:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,things at all. You just think you are. You're not really attached to them. First of all, you can't be\Nattached to them, because it's all in your head, so you're not attached to them. You're attached to the thought of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.28,0:20:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the payoff you get from it. And therefore, you don't have to surrender all these things that are so\Ndifficult to surrender. You only have to surrender one thing, and that's the willingness to let go of the payoff that you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.06,0:20:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,get out of it. You've got to let go of the payoff. The willingness. So there's only one thing we're addicted to, and\Nthat's the payoff that the ego gains out of misery, self-pity, being righteous, wrath, how I've been
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,cheated by life. Just because you're stupid and ugly doesn't mean you've been cheated by life.\NShort, stupid, and stupid. Short and ugly, that's an easy one. Where's Niko? Now stand up, Niko. Look, I love this t-shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.15,0:21:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this t-shirt. There's a man who was short and ugly, Socrates. One of the greatest names in history, and\Nrenowned for being bad looking. But I just thought, that's the greatest name in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.75,0:21:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Greatest t-shirt. It just knocked me out when I got here this morning. Quotes from Socrates on the back and Socrates on the front.\NAll right, so instead of indulging in self-pity, Socrates really changed the lives of many people. And through Socratic
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.30,0:21:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding is the quickest way to forgiveness. So people who are hung up on anger and resentment and all, or guilt, all those\Ndepend on forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.59,0:21:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the course of\Nmiracles addresses forgiveness. The 12 step groups address it. But I think the key to it is Socrates' statement, that all men can only
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.98,0:22:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,choose the good. All men choose only what they perceive to be the good. And that reveals the innate innocence within\Nconsciousness itself. How can you forgive people? Because intrinsically, they are innocent. Intrinsically, they can't discern
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.39,0:22:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,perception from essence.\NIntrinsically, this seems to be the good. So if blowing up people is the greatest good, then you can be sure they're going to be out there blowing up people. And of course they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.14,0:22:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Blowing up people, because that's where you make God happy, I guess. Okay. All right. Anyway, that's out of the naivete, the intrinsic innocence. Because the human mind by its very design is\Nunable to discern.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.83,0:22:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\Ntruth from falsehood. The human mind is unable to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.35,0:22:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It can go with likelihood. It can go with facts.\NThe difficulty with facts is nobody knows what they mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.37,0:23:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the facts. It's discerning how to assemble them and derive a meaning.\NAnd facts, even then, you don't have truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.54,0:23:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because truth is a different dimension than facts.\NFacts have nothing to do with truth. Facts are just little bits of info.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.56,0:23:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Little bits of info. Now you put them together and you extract some kind of a meaning.\NThen you have to extract significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.86,0:23:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So even though you start within the linear domain, you quickly jump to the non-linear.\NBecause meaning, significance, value, and truth are abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.04,0:23:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot measure them.\NTherefore, the cynic really...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.50,0:23:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,...really can't understand truth because they operate from lower mind, which is concrete and literal.\NYou can get the facts right, but then totally miss what they mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.79,0:24:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only quizzical emails we get are from people who cannot see the forest for the trees, you see.\NThey tend to get literal and concrete.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.49,0:24:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And thereby miss the point.\NSo the purpose of kinesiology is not to prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.83,0:24:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt's not to base anything I say on kinesiology at all, other than what the numbers come up with when you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.18,0:24:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth from which I'm speaking stands on its own.\NIt stems from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.94,0:24:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It originated at age three in a very startling, shocking, and overwhelming way.\NIt then reoccurred later on in different contexts during teenage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.32,0:24:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it then recurred even more severely later on.\NIn the very depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.65,0:24:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And since that time, the mind really says nothing.\NThinkingness can occur if it's an occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.10,0:25:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And thinkingness is possible.\NBut it's not the source of one's information.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.44,0:25:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of one's information, you know, shines forth spontaneously of its own.\NThis week I was walking out to feed the chickens or something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.62,0:25:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it became shockingly obvious.\NThat the self, the personal self, is reborn every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.45,0:25:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NAnd I went, wowzy, wowzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.75,0:25:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wowzy.\NI didn't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.33,0:25:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't thinking about anything.\NI wasn't thinking about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.68,0:25:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Going out to feed the chickens.\NThat's all I was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.04,0:25:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And that the personal self is not continuous and linear.\NThat's a retrospective falsification.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.96,0:25:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a movie.\NThere's this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.60,0:25:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this scene.\NThen this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.50,0:25:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this scene.\NThen this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.40,0:26:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you play it all together and it looks like every instant.\NThe self is reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.49,0:26:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness.\NRecreated.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.33,0:26:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,From instant to instant.\NSo you're not stuck with the linearity at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.04,0:26:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The opportunity to become enlightened is...\NDid you miss it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.53,0:26:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do that again.\NThe opportunity to become enlightened is...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.18,0:26:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the halos around everybody's head.\NThe room lit up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.18,0:26:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NCan you prove that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.93,0:26:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.\NExperientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.93,0:26:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it so?\NIt's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.69,0:26:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you go into an infinite state, it's in an instant.\NIt's in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.31,0:26:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no prodroma.\NIt doesn't get more and more and then become the greatest, the morest.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.79,0:27:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not at all that.\NAnd then it's totally that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.20,0:27:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause as soon as you turn off the movie machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.30,0:27:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Frames stop.\NThere you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.28,0:27:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So the infinite sense of self, with a capital S,\Nthe source of one's own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.87,0:27:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is always continuously present.\NAlways continuously present.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.34,0:27:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's emergence.\NIt merely awaits the dropping of energizing the desire for experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.56,0:27:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we're addicted to experiencing.\NIt isn't just the payoff of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.76,0:27:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the experiencing of that.\NSo this probe, this experiencer, with its ravenous hunger,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.11,0:28:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is always out there seeking to avoid what it senses inside as a nothingness.\NIt thinks without somethingness, it'll be left with nothingness and cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.08,0:28:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it chooses to reign.\NThe narcissistic ego doesn't believe in God.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.15,0:28:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks it is God.\NIt is the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.67,0:28:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the source of your experiencer.\NAnd the narcissistic ego is, therefore, threatened by divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.65,0:28:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's threatened by divinity.\NIt hates divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.79,0:28:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll do anything to avoid divinity.\NIn fact, any reference to divinity is now illegal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.34,0:28:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we don't mention a certain name here.\NFor fear we will offend somebody and make them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.44,0:28:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, not uncomfortable.\NI don't want to make anybody uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.48,0:29:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, please, Lord.\NNow, you all have a duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.31,0:29:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,People confuse spirituality with passivity, milksopism.\NSpirituality requires courage to stand up for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.97,0:29:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you all have a duty, which I'll give you today.\NThe Constitution of the United States says,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.32,0:29:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of the divinity of our source, we are all equal.\NBy virtue of the divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.08,0:29:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of the divinity of our creator.\NLet the Congress not establish any religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.18,0:29:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,nor, nor prohibit the free practice thereof.\NYou notice how cleverly the second half of the sentence is never mentioned?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.03,0:30:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor prohibit the free practice thereof.\NSuch as putting a Christmas tree on your lawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.14,0:30:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.\NAnyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.10,0:30:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor prohibit.\NNor prohibit the free practice thereof.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.54,0:30:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, instead of a peace parade, I would appreciate it if you would write your congressman, your senator, Bill O'Reilly, the president, whoever.\NYou seem to have forgotten the second part of the sentence in the United States Constitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.28,0:30:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NSo, even those that are pro-maintaining the establishment of religious as a core essence of society,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.46,0:30:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves don't even know it, or ignore it.\NIsn't that a...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.00,0:31:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you get anywhere if you don't know the truth?\NAnd secondly, if you don't stand up for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.56,0:31:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't win with wimpism.\NWimpism.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.61,0:31:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality does not mean soppy wimpism.\NLimpy, limpy wimpism.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.67,0:31:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They take me down, they're going to have to do it against my protest.\NYeah, that's my lecture for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.87,0:31:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is going to be...\NYes, confusion of spirituality with passivity and non-action.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.46,0:31:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, non-action is an internal function.\NIt's not an external action.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.13,0:31:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-action means one automatically reflects the truth to the greatest understanding of which they are capable.\NTo facilitate the development of the spiritual awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.47,0:32:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend generally contemplation rather than meditation.\NMeditation has its place.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.69,0:32:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very intense, it's very precise.\NBut it's usually done in this corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.07,0:32:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,with these flowers and this incense and these bells and gongs.\NAnd now when it's over,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.96,0:32:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddamn neighbors, what the hell are they wearing the raver?\NIt becomes compartmentalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.23,0:32:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it isn't who you are, it's what you do.\NUnderstand how meditation...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.93,0:32:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I know zillions of people that meditate.\NAnd they really aren't much farther than they were when they started.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.84,0:32:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Including pranayama, which calibrates at 2.30.\NSo if you're expecting pranayama to get you to heaven, it's going to be a slow trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.93,0:33:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a way of being in the world.\NSo spirituality is a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.90,0:33:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how you are.\NWith...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,With your own existence, in the here and now.\NOrdinary vision focuses on the near side of an object because it intends to manipulate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.62,0:33:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A contemplative lifestyle focuses on the far side of objects because it's inclusive.\NYou see, if I'm going to do something with these flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.80,0:33:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I focus on this, so I don't knock it over.\NUnderstand?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.88,0:33:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I'm enjoying the flowers, I get the totality of it.\NBecause I'm not going to do something with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.85,0:33:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The focus of concentrated focus is about 20 degrees.\NAbout 20 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.44,0:33:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In training the police.\NPolice are trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.97,0:34:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you focus on your opponent, your range is 20 degrees.\NAnd although you see him, you miss his accomplice here, who just shot you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.02,0:34:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't see him over there.\NSo even in police work, it's recommended to have a diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.16,0:34:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a diffuse.\NSo if you intentionally make your visual field diffuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.20,0:34:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you go from 20 degrees to 200 degrees.\NFrom 20 to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.48,0:34:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?\NTo be a certain way is contemplative in which you become one with the overall field.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.11,0:34:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You align with the context rather than the content.\NOf course, you need the specifics of content to perform a function.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.13,0:35:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm going to snip off the flower,\NI have to really focus where to have the scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.86,0:35:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But to include the beauty of the flowers in my life is total.\NIf they said, sit down and draw the flowers as you saw them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.67,0:35:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do that because I don't have that much linearity.\NFocusing on the flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.49,0:35:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So to have a contemplative way of being in the world,\Nthis becomes habitual.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.58,0:35:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As you do it, as you become contemplative,\Nas you're walking to feed the chickens,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.94,0:35:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you get the self is reborn every instant.\NGod, it's so obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.04,0:35:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So obvious.\NYou could think a thousand lifetimes and never realize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.03,0:35:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You could think 1,000 lifetimes and never realize that the self is reborn every instant.\NWe've got permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.22,0:35:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact, oh Lord.\NThat is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.28,0:36:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You live a thousand lifetimes\Nand never realize that,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.13,0:36:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\Nwhy is it reborn as what it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.86,0:36:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because for karmic reasons, the movie is playing\Nand you want to know, you want to put the next film in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.42,0:36:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your habit is to always react this way.\NSo that's the karmic propensity pulling you back into identification with the personal limited self.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.69,0:36:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The contemplative lifestyle tends to take you out of it.\NYou tend to become, who you are tends to become more diffused.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.45,0:36:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good word, diffused.\NYes, you become more diffused all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.81,0:36:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the whole room rather than one spot in the room.\NSo we'll go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.38,0:36:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, we've wandered from the chart.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.07,0:37:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,From this map of consciousness that evolved from the Gorsy Miracle students\Nwho did not go weak with fluorescent lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.52,0:37:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember that.\NAnd I thought, what's the matter with these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.90,0:37:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So if any of you have not done the course, and you're going to do the course,\Nit'd be fun just to have somebody test you looking at fluorescent lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.76,0:37:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They make 100% of you a week.\NAnd sweet and low various things over your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.36,0:37:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after you get to about less than 90 or something like that, retest yourself.\NSo we've done that with personal friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.35,0:37:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And it works.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.39,0:37:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of that, we came out with a logarithmic scale of 1 to 1,000.\NNow, the scale doesn't prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.42,0:37:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to re-contextualize kinesiology.\NKinesiology is affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.53,0:38:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you a sense of the degree of reliability, confirmation.\NIt's really a confirmatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.47,0:38:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That somebody would need.\NA scale to discern severe truth from a severe falsehood seems astonishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.56,0:38:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can see that a good part of the world is unable to differentiate.\NThat which is intrinsically classically termed evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.59,0:38:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,unable even when it's stunning them, even when it's right in their face,\Neven when it's on a poster 20 feet by 40 feet, they can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.59,0:38:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That incapacity, then, of the human mind to discern truth from falsehood,\Nis...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.30,0:38:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the kinesiologic numbers are would be\Nwhat we could call level of confidence in statistics and mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.35,0:38:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We have what's called level of confidence.\NThis is so at what level of confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.07,0:39:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We use the symbol P.\NP is less than .01, less than .001.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.32,0:39:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the more zeros you get, the greater the confidence you can put in.\NSo that mathematical statistical system is...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.82,0:39:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,parallel, comparable to what we do with kinesiology.\NThis is quicker, and so it's merely confirmatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.02,0:39:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you the level of confidence.\NSo let's say kinesiology indicates the degree of the level of confidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.78,0:39:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,actually, of spiritual truth and of reality in general.\NSo this is well known, and of course, because I was a psychiatrist for many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.17,0:39:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we put the emotions that go...\NSo with this, also the process going on in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.80,0:39:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have the law, and we have these levels,\Nand the view of yourself, and the view of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.94,0:40:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The view of God.\NAnd we really could...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.48,0:40:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The view of God, we could even have one lower than this,\Nbecause if we can go lower than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.52,0:40:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there are people who literally hate God, you know.\NAnd any mention of God, of divinity, makes them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.84,0:40:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go to the next slide.\NI hope I haven't made anybody uncomfortable this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.83,0:40:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how narcissistic this is?\NI have a problem with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.98,0:40:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that makes me uncomfortable.\NYeah, well, it makes me uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.05,0:40:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes you uncomfortable, buddy?\NIt says God over the courthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.23,0:40:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, go around the block.\NAll right, 78% of the world's population lives below the level of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.10,0:40:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See the great mass of it on this graph.\NThe number of people from 200 and up is quite limited on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.83,0:41:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that?\NWhen you look at human history, when you listen to the evening news,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.39,0:41:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you can understand why.\NSo if we put it this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.69,0:41:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that people from 200 and up are small,\Nnumerically small, numerically small.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.88,0:41:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,However, because of their relative power,\Nthey offset.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.92,0:41:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The negativity of the 78%.\NSo without these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.16,0:41:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,life would have destroyed itself.\NWithout the teachings of the avatars,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.28,0:41:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind would have long ago destroyed itself.\NMankind would have exterminated itself a long, long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.89,0:41:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the hydrogen bomb gave us a great, you know,\Nwith the hydrogen bomb, we could have done it very neatly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.25,0:42:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and got it over all at once.\NEvolution of consciousness, I see, is going up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.50,0:42:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For those who predict the end of the world and all kinds of negativity,\Nthat's really quite in opposition to consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.74,0:42:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness of life and mankind in particular\Nis advancing at an extremely rapid rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.66,0:42:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if the world's going to end pretty soon,\Nwe'll all be enlightened before it does, so who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.54,0:42:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to talk about spiritual teachers and teachings.\NBut I'm just doing a fast recapitulation
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.36,0:42:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who haven't been here before,\Nthat these are the earth epics,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.87,0:42:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the evolution of life beginning.\NAnd it's important to understand this
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.02,0:43:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because that way you can see the innocence of the ego.\NYou can see that the emergence,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.83,0:43:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the emergence of life required tenacity\Nin order to maintain life in a planet
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.60,0:43:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in which things did not come in neat packages as frozen.\NThe little bacteria has to nibble around
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.37,0:43:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and find out what smells good and tastes good.\NThe little amoeba has to find out what's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.93,0:43:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So that same little processor we call the experiencer\Nis still within the human ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.95,0:43:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It was necessary to the evolution of life,\Nso we'll go to the next chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.85,0:43:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can stop feeling guilty about the ego\Nbecause without it you wouldn't be alive
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.28,0:43:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel guilty about the ego.\NWasn't for the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.52,0:43:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see the evolution of life through the animal kingdom.\NAnd I'll say, please don't send me a questionnaire
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.96,0:44:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,about the dolphins and the whales again.\NBy God, this month somebody did again.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.50,0:44:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this month somebody did again. Somebody did again. Oh, well. The purpose is not the specifics.\NThe specifics, you know, I'm afraid people get lost in the trees. We're looking at a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.42,0:44:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,forest. The forest is to show the evolution of consciousness over great eons of time,\Nto show its expression throughout the animal kingdom in an evolutionary way, so we can
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.40,0:44:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,see how the brain function then was aligned with animal survival, and therefore the animal\Ninstincts about which we all feel guilty are intrinsic and built in because that was the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.47,0:45:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,source of life. Then you see at level 200, it's quite significant, life goes from the\Npredatory, these are all primarily predatory, not 100% predatory, but as a lifestyle, and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.74,0:45:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we move to the benign herbivore. So these from 200 and up tend to be more benign. You're\Nstill not safe with a chimpanzee, he can tear you to pieces, but don't play with him, don't
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.95,0:45:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,fool with him. Nevertheless, the quality of life, the quality of life changes. So we'll\Ngo to the next, and of course the dog's wagging tail and the cat's purr, and now there's some
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.18,0:46:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,frequency range and vibration of a cat's purr is therapeutic to osteoporosis. So as you\Nget a recording of a cat's purr, if you're old and shrimpy like I am, and you play this
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.99,0:46:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,cat's purr sound in here, you know, very interesting things. Then life evolved to thinkingness.\NThinkingness. The difficulty was that the animal instincts, with the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.24,0:46:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,emergence of the prefrontal cortex, the prefrontal cortex was now utilized in the service of\Nthe animal instincts. So instead of eliminating the animal and replacing it with the prefrontal
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.02,0:46:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,cortex, which is uniquely human, it was added on. Therefore, now life had a new and more\Npotent weapon than it ever had before. It used to have only teeth and claws, now it's
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.41,0:46:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,got intelligence. It's got atomic bombs, it's got weapons.\NIt's got fanaticism. You can now get the animal roused with fanaticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.28,0:47:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Fanaticism. Finally, the domination of the animal recedes and you can think more and more clearly\Nwithout the interference of emotionality. This is the emergence of really the basis of our entire
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.74,0:47:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,civilization, beginning back in ancient Greece, 350 BC, 500 BC, or anything like that, and then this is\Nthere the capacity to think so the great books of the Western world represent the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.33,0:47:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,attempt of man to use the intellect to discern the truth without the\Ninterference of emotionality positionality opinion political
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.57,0:47:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,persuasions etc they did a great University of Chicago did a great job\Nwith it with the exception as I always point out you see they're all in the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.10,0:47:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,mid 400s and almost up to 500 and they're in the middle of it you see\Nmarks at 130 I guess they put him in there because at the time they were
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.38,0:48:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,doing that communism was a very influential and angles at 200 so if you\Ntake these two people out the totality jumps from like 450 to 465 and because
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.22,0:48:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the deviations that we now see is what is called relativism\Nin which there is no such thing as truth there's only positionality that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.14,0:48:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,was started by Karl Marx okay now we'll move to the next but here's the great\Nminds that form the structure of society I like the Heisenberg principle the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.99,0:48:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,thing I like about quantum mechanics you see we went from the differential\Ncalculus Newton who discovered the basic laws of physics basic laws of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.83,0:49:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,physics and movement of the planets tremendous the next major jump then was\Nthe quantum mechanics which is a different paradigm you can't apply the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.47,0:49:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm Newtonian physics it's a quantum mechanics so not only is you see\Ntruth is only true within a certain paradigm and great errors are made by
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.35,0:49:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,people who misapply things that are true in this paradigm but they are not true\Nin this paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.05,0:49:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,misapply it to a different paradigm in which is inappropriate think about\Nquantum mechanics is neat is it brings in for the first time the importance of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.60,0:49:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the function of consciousness itself and of course we're all very familiar with\Nthe basic experiments that to repeat it you cannot get the same answer twice
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.46,0:49:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because having looked at it one time the mirror looking at it you've brought in\Nthe influence of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.72,0:50:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've now changed now changed the potential so the Heisenberg principle of\Ncourse is the scientific corollary to spiritual work spiritual work the power
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.41,0:50:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of intention when there is book the power of intention intention then\Ngreatly influences the results and when we do consciousness research what we're
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.03,0:50:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,very frequently picking up is that the personal\Nthere
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.03,0:50:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,they calibrated a certain thing because of their intention so you know if I\Nsometimes we get static kind of email and the first thing I want to know is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.27,0:50:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it calibrating I don't want to even read it I'd say you know what is\Nthis calibrated that gives me a certain expectation of what the verses motive is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.11,0:50:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,why are they writing this because people who have an honest question ask you a\Nquestion that people who are just out to give you static make a hostile statement
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.51,0:51:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with two different things altogether\Nnow the influence of intention then to my understanding would be greatly
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.28,0:51:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,influenced by the power of consciousness of the observer would not you see an\Nexperiment the most walks by and looks at it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.20,0:51:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what how much will it change if you put a monkey and monkey looks at it how much\Nwould it change if you put a human being looks at it now you put somebody was
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.24,0:51:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,very spiritually advanced and looks at it\NNow you see why the 15% balance the 85%.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.27,0:51:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because their power is such that by their intention,\Nthey counterbalance the negativity of 85% of the world's population.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.10,0:52:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg Principle, then, is that the potential collapse of the wave function\Nfrom potentiality to actuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.69,0:52:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that is something you perceive as you advance in consciousness.\NYou get beyond cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.42,0:52:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no this causing of that.\NThe whole idea of causality is in the 400s, the Newtonian paradigm of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.60,0:52:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is a this causing of that.\NIf you follow a contemplative lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.78,0:52:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and give up the bad habit of thinking about everything that you see,\Njust witness it,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.91,0:52:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll notice that one thing emerges into another.\NThings change and emerge.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.95,0:52:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see any causality.\NThe causality you made up in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.80,0:52:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw the flower blossom.\NDid you see causality?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.70,0:53:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the causality?\NI don't see any causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.97,0:53:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw potentiality manifesting as actuality.\NIt is not based on causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.65,0:53:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not based on cause.\NIt is based on emergence,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.05,0:53:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because the nature of creation is evolutionary.\NYou don't see something causing something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.22,0:53:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think in terms of cause,\Nyou end up with an intellectual limitation
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.50,0:53:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and great difficulty with theology,\Nwhich you then have to presume that there is an initial cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.82,0:53:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If life is a whole sequence, an infinite number of causes,\Nthen you end up with the...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.88,0:54:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the error of the presumption of the principle of a first cause,\Nwhich is presumed to be divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.51,0:54:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to look at divinity as the atmosphere\Nwhich allows what develops to develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.80,0:54:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the sea, the fish would not.\NBut the sea does not cause the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.42,0:54:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea doesn't cause the fish.\NThey provide the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.29,0:54:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the emergence of evolution can express itself.\NThus, divinity is...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.49,0:54:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the infinite field of consciousness\Nin which all potentiality has the option of becoming an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.18,0:54:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And it does so by a number of mechanisms.\NOne is by the Heisenberg principle, by intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.58,0:54:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention to become enlightened, then,\Nis a powerful driving force beyond your awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.72,0:55:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of all the teachings, lectures, books, videos, etc.,\Nis one thing and one thing only.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.24,0:55:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is to reach enlightenment.\NThere's no other reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.55,0:55:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't say it to benefit the oil companies.\NI don't say it to benefit a political party.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.62,0:55:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have set up a whole structure of understanding,\Nreally, for the first time in human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.24,0:55:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that supports the evolution of human consciousness to enlightenment.\NThat's the only purpose of it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.96,0:55:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is to support the evolution of consciousness,\Nto reach the state of enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.79,0:55:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,reach the state called enlightenment.\NTo become more and more conscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.75,0:55:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to support the advance of consciousness.\NBecause then consciousness of its own,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.45,0:55:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own, without being asked,\Ndon't have to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.88,0:55:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You just go out to feed the chickens.\NAnd it says, the self is reborn every instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.58,0:56:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout all the time it's been doing that.\NThroughout all the time it's been rebirthing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.38,0:56:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Every instant.\NAnd you remember, at a certain level,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.56,0:56:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you start remembering lifetimes.\NYou remember lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.57,0:56:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's not really remembering.\NIt's like you go back into the lifetime and it reruns.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.67,0:56:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like what's happening now.\NIt isn't like a movie where you witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.35,0:56:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,nor is it like a memory.\NYou can reactivate that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.09,0:56:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's simple ways of doing it, simple self-hypnosis.\NI can tell anybody how to reactivate a past lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.88,0:56:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's extremely simple.\NWith profound relaxation done,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.06,0:56:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because of your intention,\Nyou say, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.72,0:56:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get along with horses.\NI don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.30,0:56:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never had any problem with horses in this lifetime.\NNever abused them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.29,0:57:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet horses have practically done me in.\NI've been thrown,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.49,0:57:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,stomped,\Nraked up the back of the horse
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.01,0:57:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and on a bridge,\Nknocked out and unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.38,0:57:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what's with me and horses?\NSo, in questioning that, I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.62,0:57:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go into a profound state of relaxation.\NNow, when you go into self-hypnosis,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.20,0:57:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to be very, very profound,\Nrelaxed, complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.51,0:57:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think you're completely and totally relaxed,\Nyou aren't yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.67,0:57:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's more profound than that.\NIt's a profound relaxation.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.67,0:57:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In that state, the question is, I want to know.\NYou can use any device.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.42,0:57:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, I will walk up this hill and over the horizon.\NAnd then all of a sudden,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.24,0:57:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you re-experience, re-experience the life.\NYou don't remember the life.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.40,0:57:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't edit it because it's running like a movie.\NYou can't edit it with the movie's playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.55,0:57:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then that life is recalled.\NAnd the explanation of what you're hung up on
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.53,0:58:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime now becomes quite clear.\NIt's a useful technique
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.35,0:58:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,if you get up against a difficult block.\NVery often, intuitively,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.25,0:58:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that something must have accounted for that.\NIf everybody's cheating you all your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.39,0:58:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be wrong.\NYou can be sure that in some lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.79,0:58:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you were cheating the hell out of everybody.\NYou have to forgive the one in you who didn't know any better
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.79,0:58:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and place their survival on dishonesty.\NAnd you try to make amends for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.17,0:58:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to, anyway, you take responsibility.\NSo one of the things about spiritual evolution is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.84,0:58:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,always to take responsibility.\NNever assume it's caused by something out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.14,0:58:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,even more backwards in time.\NThe greatest value of Est for those that,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.66,0:58:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that you did Est,\Nwas that it wouldn't allow you to get away
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.90,0:58:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with any alibi or excuse.\NYou just had to take responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.90,0:59:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for whatever it was, you know.\NIf your shoelace broke,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.05,0:59:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,why did you do that?\NYou had to take responsibility for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.46,0:59:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the human ego hates to take responsibility.\NTakes responsibility that you're not,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.04,0:59:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,not that you're the cause,\Nbut you're the source of it and you're activating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.62,0:59:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're giving energy to that belief system.\NWhere were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.31,0:59:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to complete before the first break.\NHow much time we got?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.90,0:59:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.02,0:59:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll come.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.02,0:59:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll complete,\NI want to complete all the academic,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.02,0:59:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all the slides.\NAll this has been covered in books and charts and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.90,0:59:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very important to know.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.26,0:59:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it recontextualizes the way you see yourself\Nand the way you see spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.24,0:59:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way you envision the world,\Nyour perceptions of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.38,0:59:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of good and bad, good and evil,\Ngood and evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.56,1:00:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you really get hung up on good and evil.\NAll you can,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.16,1:00:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,instead, all you can see is that people innocently\Nare blindly following what they believe to be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.16,1:00:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They're blindly following the highest good.\NSometimes the highest good is to steal a pie from the bakery
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.90,1:00:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because you haven't got any money.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.10,1:00:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest good, that's the best you could do.\NYou've got your choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.78,1:00:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go hungry or you steal a pie.\NSo you might say honesty isn't even possible
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.62,1:00:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,until you reach a certain level of self-sufficiency, right?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.84,1:00:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there could be a good time you could sacrifice yourself\Nfor God and starve to death,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.03,1:00:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which I don't know would make God very happy,\Nbut it makes a lot of martyrs feel happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.29,1:00:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the brain, as you see at the top,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.62,1:00:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've done this before,\Nthe brain up to consciousness level 200
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.52,1:00:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,operates in a different way\Nthan the brain from consciousness level 200 and over,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.32,1:01:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which is another reason to forgive people\Nbecause below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.22,1:01:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the way the person's brain works.\NYou know, the input, the perception,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.42,1:01:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,goes through the thalamus, the emotional relay,\Nvery rapidly to the emotional center,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.32,1:01:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole thing is over.\NAnd in that process, they release adrenaline,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.22,1:01:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,fight or flight.\NSo this is an animal response.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.72,1:01:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This part of the brain is what dominates 85% of mankind.\NEighty-five percent of mankind is dominated by the animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.64,1:01:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by the animal.\NCannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.33,1:01:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Cannot tell a savior from a narcissistic megalomaniac dictator\Nwho's going to blow you all to kingdom come.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.72,1:01:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the crowds over the generations saluting people.\NThey're calibrated at 80.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.12,1:01:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated at 80.\NWhoa.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.53,1:02:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the same time, we see society ridiculing\Nthat which calibrates to the thousand divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.03,1:02:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ.\NLet's not mention these things in public.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.83,1:02:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be on the side of pedophilia,\Nbut it's not okay to mention God or have a Christmas tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.88,1:02:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called the Lucifer conversion,\Nthe inability to believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.08,1:02:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The inability to tell the truth from falsehood.\NIn which the good becomes the bad,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.48,1:02:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bad becomes the good, yeah.\NAll right, that happens in this kind of a brain, all right,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.31,1:02:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because divinity threatens the narcissistic core of the ego,\Nwhich presumes itself to be the source of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.51,1:02:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You spend your whole spiritual life trying to transcend\Nthe narcissist ego and its payoffs, its belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.16,1:02:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you finally transcend all the levels,\NI know what the core of the ego is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.80,1:03:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it got hit by the very core of it.\NYou've got nothing left.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.92,1:03:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is silent.\NThere are no others.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.82,1:03:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All these spiritual things talking about others,\Nvisions and others talking to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.38,1:03:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As you go there, there's no one.\NThere's only yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.68,1:03:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no others coaching you along the way.\NYou don't hear visions, angelic teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.39,1:03:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind becomes silent.\NThere's nothing left except life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.76,1:03:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only yourself.\NThere's only God.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.18,1:03:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one thing left when you get to the last doorway.\NAnd that is life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.79,1:03:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing left that you're clinging to.\NYou're clinging to life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.27,1:03:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're facing the very core of the ego.\NFew people know the core of the ego because they've never faced it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.27,1:04:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're facing it, you're facing the certainty\Nthat if you surrender this, you will die.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.65,1:04:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never faced it.\NNever.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.75,1:04:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never faced it.\NPhysical death is a joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.75,1:04:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Whooping you out of the body.\NAnd there it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.75,1:04:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sitting here.\NDumb looking thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.84,1:04:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So stupid looking.\NAnybody know this?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.84,1:04:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Been out of the body.\NAnybody here been out of the body?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.97,1:04:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou know how dumb the body looks.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.97,1:04:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It lays there.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.97,1:04:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where you're really up against the nitty-gritty now.\NBecause realize the last thing that you haven't surrendered to God is your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.57,1:04:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You've surrendered your life pattern, your life habits, your life beliefs.\NBut not life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.82,1:04:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And then comes an absolute terror.\NAs you surrender life, the knowingness, which I'm repeating now, which was known at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.84,1:04:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it, is a vibration and a frequency in the aura because your mind is silent.\NWalk straight ahead no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.58,1:04:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is illusion.\NIt's safe to let go of your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.77,1:05:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can tell you that with a frequency and a vibration who hasn't done it.\NSo with absolute terror, and for a few moments you die, and it is an agony of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.34,1:05:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You agonizingly die.\NAnd then it shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.23,1:05:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite splendor.\NInfinite splendor of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.48,1:05:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind is struck silent.\NThe mind is struck silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.87,1:05:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That was what the ego dreaded all this time.\NThat's what the ego dreaded all this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.12,1:05:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it hates any mention of God.\NBecause it is the source of your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.19,1:05:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what comes up.\NYou are so firmly convinced that the ego is your source of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.19,1:05:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd rather go through all kinds of tortures, endless lifetimes of hell, agony,\Nrather than let it go.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.99,1:06:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego has you convinced.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.05,1:06:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because since the beginning of life, the first bacteria, that was true.\NThat was a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.05,1:06:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that you're not an amoeba.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.66,1:06:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Destiny as a human being is to transcend identification\Nand limitation of the linear animal world.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.66,1:06:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you go over 200 now, the brain physiology changes.\NThe prefrontal cortex now begins to play a greater part.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.96,1:06:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course the most important thing that happens at 200\Nis the emergence of the kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.96,1:06:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the kundalini energy, which we've spoken of before,\Nis a very unique spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.96,1:06:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200 and up now, the spiritual energy shines forth.\NIt runs up through, classically described as running up through the chakra system.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.22,1:07:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's a radiance from within.\NAnd this radiance transforms perception and understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.25,1:07:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and how you see and experience the world.\NAnd as we've mentioned, in the high 500s,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.25,1:07:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it brings on the so-called siddhis,\Nwhich are sort of paranormal phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.25,1:07:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the miraculous, capacity for the miraculous.\NSo this now, the most important thing about this
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.25,1:07:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you develop an etheric brain.\NUnder 200, you don't have an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.50,1:07:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, you have an etheric brain.\NUnder 200, there is group karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.50,1:07:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Above 200, there's individual karma.\NThat's a rather profound statement.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.52,1:07:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask that for this group.\NThat statement is a fact, Lord, and resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.52,1:07:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Add a level of confidence of 1,000.\NAbsolute level of confidence, then, it says.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.39,1:08:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That is so. That is so.\NIt explains mass phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.55,1:08:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people will come in, then, as a group,\Nnot as an individual.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.12,1:08:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a mass of birds like that,\Nthey share an individual unit.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.12,1:08:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,One, they share the same karma.\NYou're not seeing 10,000 different bird karmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.12,1:08:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They share a oneness.\NThe oneness of the group dominates.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.25,1:08:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200 now, you have a unique personal karma.\NOver 200, one of that bird is going to be different
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.44,1:08:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,than the rest of the birds.\NIt's destined now to go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.64,1:08:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThis is a level of consciousness and social problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.49,1:08:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We say,\Nthe way to integrity is to stop blaming anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.48,1:08:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Not blaming anybody.\NJust start from where you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.09,1:09:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't necessary to blame.\NLet's just see how that feeds the ego and weakens you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.09,1:09:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares if somebody is to blame?\NSo what?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.98,1:09:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.98,1:09:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You lost your thumb, you lost it.\NIt's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.62,1:09:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't play the piano.\NDid it have a karmic precedent?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.72,1:09:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure did.\NIt sure did.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.20,1:09:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure did.\NNothing just happens by accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.26,1:09:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo we take, then, responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.26,1:09:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the level of consciousness moves up,\Nyou see that happiness is not related to out-there-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.26,1:09:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's related to level of consciousness.\NWe see the happiness rate is concordant
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.26,1:09:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,with level of consciousness.\NUp here, you don't need anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.87,1:10:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have an apple and a cock to sleep on\Nand be completely happy and delighted.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.87,1:10:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At a lower level, you can have millions and commit suicide.\NOkay, we'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.80,1:10:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to finish all the academic,\Nfor those who haven't been here before.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.76,1:10:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next slide.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.81,1:10:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, this is the same thing,\Nexpressed somewhat differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.83,1:10:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you see is below the level of 200,\Nthis line should really be,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.83,1:10:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,crossed here,\Nbelow the level of 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.83,1:10:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how the rate of happiness drops off.\NSo although there's temporary gain,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.83,1:10:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the pleasure in hating people,\Npleasure in feeling sorry for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.83,1:10:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasure in getting even,\Npleasure in blowing up a busload of children,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.83,1:10:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not actual happiness.\NIt's only once you cross over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.83,1:10:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You see automatically it jumps,\Njust at 200, then at 250.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.83,1:11:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As you go up,\Nyou see the rate of happiness finally reaches 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.83,1:11:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You finally reach a condition\Nin which your inner state
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.24,1:11:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely immune to the external world.\NThey say,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.76,1:11:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they say,\Nyou're going to be shot tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.76,1:11:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, all right, okay.\NIt just doesn't make any difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.95,1:11:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you experience that stage,\Nyou'll know what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.11,1:11:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the inner is so complete\Nthat what happens in the inner
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.24,1:11:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and the outer is irrelevant.\NYou know, it's convenient.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.33,1:11:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a convenience.\NYeah, if you die in the snow,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.33,1:11:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you die in the snow.\NAnd if you don't, you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.56,1:11:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I remember climbing in a big bank of snow,\NI've told this story many times,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.56,1:11:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as a teenager.\NAnd just to get out of the wind
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.56,1:11:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and the blizzard,\Nit was pitch black,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.56,1:11:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,10 below zero in the blizzard.\NAnd I reached, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.65,1:11:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I dug out in the hole in the snow,\Nit was all crusty,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.65,1:12:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,this big pile of snow,\Ndug a little cave
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.65,1:12:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and went in there.\NAnd then,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.61,1:12:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,oh God, yeah.\NIt was being dissolved
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.48,1:12:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,into an infinite presence of love\Nbeyond all description.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.48,1:12:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It dissolved all sense of personal self.\NIt dissolved time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.83,1:12:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It dissolved physicality.\NIt dissolved anticipation.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.65,1:12:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether the body survived or breathed or not\Nwas totally irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.65,1:12:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not even interesting.\NPeople say,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.45,1:12:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, what if I keep doing spiritual work?\NI might die or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.52,1:12:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, when that comes,\Nyou don't care whether you die or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.52,1:12:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not going to be a problem.\NIt's not going to be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.52,1:12:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The personal self dies\Nbecause it's excess baggage.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.52,1:12:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you sit down in excess baggage.\NDid we do all the slides?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.96,1:13:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She keeps them secret.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.04,1:13:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we did the rate of happiness, yes.\NYou've got to move along
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.06,1:13:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because by the break we're going to have that.\NEh?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.06,1:13:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NWell, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.88,1:13:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can slow down.\NSo now we can move faster.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.74,1:13:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's put it up.\NLet's put it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.74,1:13:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's where we ended last time.\NSo we're beginning there,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.84,1:13:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,those of you who are linear\Nand able to follow things
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.84,1:13:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from one thing to the other.\NNo, before that we had
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.06,1:13:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,31 characteristics of spiritual integrity.\NOh, we do have it, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.56,1:13:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NWe're going to finish that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.90,1:13:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to finish that by what time?\NIn five minutes?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.90,1:13:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Five minutes.\NOh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.90,1:13:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right.\NIt's only 31 points.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.90,1:13:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We can cover that in five minutes.\NNo, we've distilled, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.19,1:14:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with consciousness research then,\Nyou can distill the degree of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.19,1:14:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,purity, level of consciousness\Nof anything or anyone anywhere in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.38,1:14:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just through intuitive knowingness,\Nanybody with any kind of spiritual intuitive knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.38,1:14:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,would be able to come up with the same chart.\NWe wanted to, without naming specifics,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.64,1:14:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to differentiate\Nintegrous teachers and organizations
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.64,1:14:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from those which deviate\Nfrom the straight and narrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.64,1:14:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When people read my books,\Nthe first thing, trouble they have
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.82,1:14:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is they've got to get past\NGloria and Excelsior's deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.08,1:14:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second tripper I put in there,\Nthe second mind is called
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.08,1:14:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,straight and narrow is the path.\NSo this is straight and narrow is the path,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.08,1:14:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, because that which is complete\Nand total within itself has no needs,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.27,1:14:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,has no needs.\NSo you can tell the spiritual integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.27,1:15:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,from lack of integrity\Nby the degree of neediness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.27,1:15:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that it presents to the world.\NProselytizing, trying to get you to sign up,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.40,1:15:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,take oaths, swear on things.\NThat which is non-integrous is seeking gain,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.92,1:15:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is looking for gain.\NIt wants to influence you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.92,1:15:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to enroll you,\Ndominate you, control you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.92,1:15:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we don't invite anybody\Nto follow our work.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.37,1:15:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not invite anyone here,\Nnor do I even recommend
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.66,1:15:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that you follow this work at all.\NYou're either dragged to it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.94,1:15:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or you're not.\NBut we certainly don't try to
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.20,1:15:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,sell anybody on it.\NWe don't want anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.71,1:16:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,selling, enthusing, signing up,\Nmulti-level marketing.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.28,1:16:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want anybody to take any oaths.\NThat was an oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.89,1:16:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,More or less.\NPrevious lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.50,1:16:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,one lecture got together.\NAll took the same oath
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.66,1:16:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,about 300 years ago.\NHere's another author.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.66,1:16:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two authors here today.\NWe had four authors here
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.20,1:16:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,one time in Canada.\NWe say take no oaths.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.20,1:16:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause you don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.20,1:16:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what the long-term consequence is.\NYou say, if I ever so-and-so,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.36,1:16:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,may the reverse be my lot.\NIt is.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.36,1:16:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually it's if you leave them.\NLeave them.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.40,1:16:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You will get a rattlesnake\Nin your mailbox or
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.49,1:16:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,some horrible thing will befall you.\NWell, when you make an oath,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.49,1:16:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you're bound by yourself.\NNot bound by out-there-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.49,1:17:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just bound yourself.\NNow, three, four lifetimes later
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.20,1:17:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is payback time.\NSo, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.74,1:17:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God I only promised one thumb.\NCould have been worse things
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.67,1:17:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you could have promised, you know.\NOne ear.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.72,1:17:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If I write this oath,\Nmay I lose 50% of my assets.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.28,1:17:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see,\Nyou sold out your freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.63,1:17:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Never allow any people\Nto rule over you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.63,1:17:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are not rulers in this world.\NThere are not rulers.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.36,1:17:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That misinterpretation comes out of the\Ndownside of the classic Indian guruism.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.65,1:17:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The worship of the guru.\NBut the Western person doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.78,1:17:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the worship of the guru.\NAnd therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.84,1:18:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the exploitation of the Indian guru\Ntook place in the course
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.84,1:18:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of the last couple of decades.\NIt's all over the internet.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.84,1:18:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The exploitation.\NSo, a teacher doesn't want any power over you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.42,1:18:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't want any power at all.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.42,1:18:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who needs power\Nwhen you have all the power that is?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.84,1:18:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember in a very high state\Nwhere the knowingness came to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.90,1:18:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you know\Nyou're beyond personal karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.90,1:18:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,now that you know\Nthere is no accountability for your actions,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.90,1:18:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all power is yours only.\NAll power over the world is yours only.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.92,1:18:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course,\Nthe joke of it at the time was
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.14,1:18:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was experiencing the infinite power within\Nand I thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.14,1:18:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,no, who the hell would want power?\NWhat a drag.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.14,1:18:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You give your power over all of mankind.\NWhat a burden.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.14,1:19:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see what a horrible thing it would be?\NBecause that which is complete and total
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.14,1:19:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,has no needs,\Nincluding power, prestige, trappings, titles,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.14,1:19:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,power, prestige, trappings, titles.\NIt doesn't need theatrics, robes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.00,1:19:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't need to be Master Boom-gum-pum,\NMr. Boom-gum-pum, Mr. Boom-gum-pum.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.16,1:19:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Master Boom-gum-pum.\NYou come to ask me whether you can marry.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.75,1:19:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would a teacher be interested\Nwhether you marry or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.75,1:19:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, we have defined
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.94,1:19:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the characteristics of integrity.\NIntegrity in general.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.20,1:19:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll go back later.\NWe're going to take a break
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.20,1:19:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll go back later\Nand try to review a list of 144.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.55,1:20:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, I've got another list of about 20.\NPeople are always sending me emails.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.17,1:20:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Master King Kong Boncho\Nwho wrote a book about the end of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.17,1:20:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,coming in 32 years?\NHe's got 144 people.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.17,1:20:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And why does he have to drag this joker in?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.52,1:20:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll take a break\Nwith a sense of good humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.52,1:20:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOrder in the court.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.70,1:20:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to consult my crib notes here.\NI bring the crib notes,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.50,1:20:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,things that I want to mention\Nand then I forget the crib notes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.50,1:20:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I don't know what to do.\NAnyway, remember the bagpipes last time?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.95,1:20:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to be at St. Andrew's Episcopal Church\Nthe Sunday after Thanksgiving, November 27th.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.95,1:21:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be at St. Andrew's in Sedona,\NSt. Andrew's at the west end of town,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.49,1:21:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,100 Arroyo Pinyon Drive, anyway.\NAnd church, I think, is at 10.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.49,1:21:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NI don't know what time church starts.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.49,1:21:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, around there.\NAnother thing of interest
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.72,1:21:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because I like things that, you know, music\Nthat calibrates above 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.72,1:21:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Andrea Bocelli is going to be on December 7th.\NDecember 8th.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.72,1:21:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Channel 8 at 8.\NFor those of you in Sedona or Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.84,1:21:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And 12-8 at 8 on 8.\NAndrea Bocelli.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.94,1:21:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And he calibrates around, you know,\NI think in the book 535 or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.94,1:21:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, kind of makes you weep with the beauty of it.\NYou know, 535 and up makes you weep.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.12,1:22:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So many people wept with the bagpipes\Nand Bocelli makes you weep.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.32,1:22:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And great things.\NGreat stature and great meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.34,1:22:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the end of my list.\NJust those two things.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.63,1:22:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's it.\NI can only handle two things,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.04,1:22:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,so I only put two things on there.\N12-8 on Channel 8 at 8.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.49,1:22:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty neat, huh?\NI remember that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.78,1:22:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NWe were talking about...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.84,1:22:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Betty, what were we talking about?\NThere we were.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.00,1:22:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NWe were talking about...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.00,1:22:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We ended up last time, the generalities,\Nabout 35 different things that differentiate spiritual integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.00,1:22:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll go to a list,\Nwhich we also have in the form of a slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.00,1:22:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, someday we're going to publish a thing of all the slides.\NAll the slides.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.00,1:23:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a page of explanation in between each slide.\NBecause somehow that gives it to you in an experiential, spatial way.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.00,1:23:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And your mind sort of gets what the essence is out of it.\NSo I think the charts are useful, therefore.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.00,1:23:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We went over this last time,\Nso I'm not going to spend any time on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.79,1:23:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the general characteristics of spiritual integrity\Nthat differentiates integral spiritual groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.79,1:23:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I get so many questions about spiritual groups.\NThat's why I'm repeating it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.85,1:23:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We get a lot of emails.\NWhat about this teacher?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.85,1:23:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What about this method?\NEt cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.95,1:23:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want people to have within themselves,\Nthe capacity to differentiate on their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.04,1:23:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they out for gain?\NAre they proselytizing?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.04,1:23:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they trying to sign you up?\NIs it a subtle form of brainwashing?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.30,1:23:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Some call them training sessions.\NI really don't want to be trained by anybody but you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.26,1:24:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, a training session.\NThe value of many of these things is,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.80,1:24:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in many workshops,\Nfor which a great deal of money is charged,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.80,1:24:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can be boiled down to maybe two sentences.\NMany a workshop is built on maybe two sentences or two concepts.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.08,1:24:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then that's elaborated.\NHow to use this to get more money.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.11,1:24:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there'll be a workshop on how to become richer using this technique.\NAnd then how to win the person that you want to win.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.11,1:24:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's all the same tool.\NIt's all the same tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.11,1:24:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell it to you for nothing.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.46,1:24:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NForgiveness is the most rapid tool
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.16,1:24:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for rapid spiritual evolution.\NAnd all you have to do is ask yourself all the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.96,1:25:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,would you be willing to forgive and accept that which it is,\Nconsidering Socrates' observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.96,1:25:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a simple question.\NThen you do this over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.96,1:25:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So for $450, you can join me at some place.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.09,1:25:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus the room rate.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.89,1:25:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll just do it over and over.\NAnd then we'll get groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.40,1:25:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The six or eight of us will have individual groups.\NAnd each one of us will practice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.40,1:25:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see, all they're doing is getting you to do it.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.24,1:25:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing is only about doing it.\NYou've heard it, but do you do it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.72,1:25:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for $450, by God, you do it, don't you?\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.96,1:25:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You do it all day, then you do it in color blue,\Nthen you do it in color green,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.96,1:25:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can take any workshop and give it to you in two sentences.\NTwo sentences.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.33,1:26:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering the basic innocence of mankind,\Nwould you be willing to forgive this person or this incident
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.21,1:26:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or this company or the price of oil?\NOf course the company wants to make more money.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.44,1:26:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Exxon is a benevolent organization?\NOf course they're going to take advantage of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.30,1:26:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They're supposed to, aren't they?\NAren't they supposed to make money?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.20,1:26:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Business is called making money.\NIf you want to become a benevolent humanitarian organization,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.20,1:26:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a whole different script, isn't it?\NIf I'm president of a huge company and I start giving away money,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.68,1:27:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how long will I remain as president of the company?\NSo the bottom line of the ego is that it's lacking.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.57,1:27:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It must always get approval, get power over others, get glamour.\NAnd the media today is the world of glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.26,1:27:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan was watching one the other day,\Nand the both of us were just remarking on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.76,1:27:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, I've got the name and I just can't think of it.\NOh, reality TV, reality TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.18,1:27:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality TV is the most...\Nsuperficial, superfluous, unreal thing you've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.82,1:27:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In which artificial people are put in artificial circumstances,\Nartificially decorated, artificially...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.64,1:27:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing is 100% artificiality.\NIt's called reality TV with a small r, a small r.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.60,1:27:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's entertaining, and there's nothing wrong with being entertaining.\NSo could you forgive yourself for being entertained by reality TV?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.91,1:28:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you forgive yourself for liking the vulgar?\NCould you still love yourself even though you love that which is superficial and stupid?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.44,1:28:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you forgive yourself for chasing illusions?\NCould you forgive yourself for not knowing anything at all?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.73,1:28:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you forgive yourself for rebirthing yourself every second?\NYou rebirth yourself every split second.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.96,1:28:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's not every second.\NIt's every one ten thousandths of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.12,1:28:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When we track the perceiver, the perceiving edge,\Nthe experiencer edge of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.03,1:29:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which the amoeba needed in order to survive,\Nit's the cutting edge of the experiencer,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.01,1:29:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the front, it's like the prow of the ship\Nthat's cutting through the waves of experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.82,1:29:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go of being dominated by that,\Nno longer identifying it as the self,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.04,1:29:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the self stops rebirthing itself.\NThe presumption is,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.60,1:29:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the presumption of the innocent mind\Nis that it's at the effect of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.70,1:29:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at the effect of a linear causality.\NSo today I'm telling you,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.86,1:29:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not at the effect of a linear causality.\NIn fact, by virtue of the Heisenberg principle on tension,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.86,1:29:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you can decide not to rebirth yourself every second.\NI choose to let the finality be a finality, be a finality.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.61,1:29:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThis is supported by,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.68,1:29:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a way of being in the world,\Nwhich is a contemplative way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.68,1:30:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplative, when you're contemplative,\Nyou don't mean to do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.04,1:30:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the woods and it just is what it is.\NSo it moves you from acceptance to acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.07,1:30:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you begin to see\Nthat everything is emerging spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.07,1:30:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as the actualization of its potentiality.\NNothing is being caused by anything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.42,1:30:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.\NEvolution, then, is the unfolding of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.91,1:30:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution and creation are one and the same thing.\NIt is so simple to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.00,1:30:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you think about it, it's obvious.\NWhat did you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.45,1:30:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God created the world completely there and said,\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.64,1:30:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That comes back at the end of time.\NYou see how ridiculous that is?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.74,1:31:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence is continuously present beyond all time.\NAnd it is the birthing place
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.43,1:31:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in which potentiality becomes actuality.\NThe invocation, then, of intention
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.49,1:31:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,means that this potentiality will take precedence over this one.\NYou could have had pie or you could have had cake.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.81,1:31:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NYou see that all things are spontaneously emerging
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.72,1:31:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of that which they are.\NWhat does a thing mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.84,1:31:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It means what it is.\NMeaning and identity are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.26,1:31:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how dualistic it would be to say,\NThis means that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.26,1:31:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already split.\NThis doesn't mean this, that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.48,1:31:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This means this.\NIt just is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.80,1:32:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Its meaning is its reality.\NAnd its reality and its identity are one.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.80,1:32:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes you beyond duality and beyond linearity.\NBeyond linearity.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.19,1:32:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you accept your own reality in the same way.\NIn the same way.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.32,1:32:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not necessary to rebirth yourself every 10,000 seconds.\NYou're not bound to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.96,1:32:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a bad habit.\NMove on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.89,1:32:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOf course, there'll be a fee for telling you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.33,1:32:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We will have a workshop starting next week for $450\Nat the Wuhan Resort
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.40,1:32:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in which Baba Bumpum\Nwill take you through these two simple thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.28,1:33:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to the point of repetitious boredom.\NYou see, because truth is not something you can grab for.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.12,1:33:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something you open yourself to.\NWe've said that enlightenment is very, very yin.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.12,1:33:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment is very, very yin.\NThe ego is very, very yang.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.02,1:33:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets.\NIt drives.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.02,1:33:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It craves.\NIt grasps.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.02,1:33:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It sobs.\NIt rips its face.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.02,1:33:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo yang is very pow.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.82,1:33:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And yin is very so.\NThe contemplative lifestyle, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.28,1:33:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you make your life a prayer,\Nyour prayer is,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.67,1:33:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord God, reveal to me the truth of that which I am.\NAnd by your stance, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.92,1:33:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you can even picture your spirit\Nin the form of a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.48,1:34:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In the form of a mudra,\Nin which you walk through
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.92,1:34:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomenal world\Nas a question mark.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.16,1:34:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, something was out.\NAnd I said, dear God,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.76,1:34:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there's something out in this particular energy field,\Nin this particular person.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.76,1:34:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What could it be?\NInstantly,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.76,1:34:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness arose.\NSee, the arose,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.92,1:34:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness arises out of\Nnot knowingness, ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.92,1:34:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't really arise\Nas a linear logical sequence of thought
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.66,1:34:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because I wouldn't have had to ask the question.\NI could have figured it out myself, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.92,1:34:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.11,1:34:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go back to this\Nand then we'll go on to individuals.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.17,1:34:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Much of spiritual,\Nmuch of what goes on in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.14,1:34:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,called spiritual is slick.\NIt's very slick.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.27,1:35:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like reality TV.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.27,1:35:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality, spirituality.\NVery big.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.64,1:35:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful diaphanous girl.\NIt's a very slick magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.64,1:35:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Very slick.\NAnd most of the people
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.05,1:35:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,who write for these,\Nincluding myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.08,1:35:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are writing about spirituality.\NAbout.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.82,1:35:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not talking from the experiential.\NThey're talking from the descriptive.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.82,1:35:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Descriptive.\NSo if you understand that,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.30,1:35:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,there's that which has learned things\Nthrough inner experience
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.30,1:35:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and it comes about as a revelation.\NIt doesn't come as a revelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.30,1:35:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't come about as logic.\NIt doesn't come about as a consequence of study.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.56,1:35:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the only thing study can do\Nis expose you to a truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.56,1:35:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But then it's your application within yourself\Nthat is the payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.56,1:35:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Not reading the book.\NI'm very ignorant of religious history
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.59,1:36:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and the details of many religions.\NAnd I've tried to get more acquainted with it,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.13,1:36:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's too staggeringly detailed\Nand irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.27,1:36:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you know that E equals MC squared,\Nit comes about.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.28,1:36:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's preparatory work, you know.\NYou go through the linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.02,1:36:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's preparatory.\NBut then,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.18,1:36:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,how it is that E equals MC squared\Ncomes out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.85,1:36:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you're eating a cheese sandwich.\NGod, how simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.85,1:36:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How simple.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.33,1:36:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is true\Nis universally true throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.56,1:36:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we'll have to forget about\Nthe end of the world being in 23 years
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.56,1:36:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or 52 years or something.\NBecause that which is universally true
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.56,1:37:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is non-linear, beyond all time.\NTherefore, it is not,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.59,1:37:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it cannot be predicted.\NPrediction is within the linear causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.10,1:37:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a prediction that an angry god\Nin the year 3042
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.10,1:37:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to destroy mankind and all.\NAnd of course, the prophecies of the end of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.10,1:37:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,have been with us\Nsince even before the Old Testament.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.55,1:37:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The end of the worlders.\NThere used to be a journal called
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.55,1:37:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,End Times Review or something.\NYeah, it was back in the 70s or 80s.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.55,1:37:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It was popular.\NAnd everybody was into the end of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.55,1:37:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the 70s or 80s.\NAnd that sort of lost its popularity.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.90,1:37:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And they changed the dates,\Nbut that didn't help any.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.90,1:37:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we got new ones.\NAnd I get panicky emails, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.90,1:37:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What about this book?\NThe Prophecies of the World
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.90,1:37:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to end in the year 6082.\NAnd I say, don't let it worry you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.96,1:38:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to be around anyway.\NNon-exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.96,1:38:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do anything.\NIt's available to everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.19,1:38:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity of purpose.\NThere's nothing to gain or lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.19,1:38:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You merely want to share what you've discovered.\NSo the position from which I teach
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.51,1:38:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is very much the same as Fleming.\NHe discovered what penicillin could do.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.51,1:38:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, wow.\NBecause he saw the implication.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.64,1:38:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't sleep with it.\NHe was so excited.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.83,1:38:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Ran around for five years.\NBecause it was a different paradigm of reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.12,1:38:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,he got nowhere.\NAnd only because of World War II,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.82,1:38:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the infections killing off the soldiers,\Ndid the United States Army pay attention to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.82,1:38:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, he couldn't rest with his music,\Nwithout having played his music,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.33,1:38:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,without his song having been unsung.\NBecause he saw the value to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.33,1:38:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his motivation.\NTo share what he had learned.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.33,1:39:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For its intrinsic value to mankind.\NThat's the motivation, if there is such a thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.33,1:39:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of a teacher.\NSo the teacher is available.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.33,1:39:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity of purpose.\NDoesn't own the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.33,1:39:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Devoid of positionality.\NTruth is not anti-anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.33,1:39:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The opposite of truth, you know,\Nis the opposite of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.75,1:39:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The opposite of truth is the absence of truth.\NSo in the book, Truth vs. Falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.84,1:39:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we try to make that clear.\NThere's either truth or its absence.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.84,1:39:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like light and darkness.\NIt's not a dualistic set of opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.88,1:39:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Light is either present or not present.\NWhen it's not present, we call it darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.07,1:39:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But darkness is not the opposite of light.\NNot the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.07,1:39:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the absence.\NFalsehood is the absence.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.68,1:39:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Devoid of positionality.\NYou don't have to sign up for anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.68,1:39:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No oaths, no rules.\NNon-controlling.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.68,1:39:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't want to control what you should wear or eat.\NNo force or intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.87,1:40:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one.\NThen we'll go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.25,1:40:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-binding.\NYou don't have to sign up for anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.41,1:40:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's free to come or go.\NEverybody's free to either listen or not listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.53,1:40:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspirational.\NNon-materialistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.53,1:40:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-fulfilling.\NThe work should be,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.98,1:40:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tried to make the work that I do,\Nso complete and total,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.98,1:40:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that's bulwarked.\NIt's bulwarked.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.98,1:40:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NEven if you don't believe in this or that,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.98,1:40:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the bulwark keeps it from being misinterpreted\Nat a later date.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.98,1:40:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-dualistic.\NOkay, move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.96,1:40:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-dualistic.\NMeans that it's non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.96,1:40:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-linear.\NThe absolute truth is beyond linearity.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.96,1:40:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Linearity is what?\NDefinition and time and place and specifics.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.96,1:40:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And truth is beyond all that.\NThat which is linear is confined
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.04,1:41:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to the consciousness level of the 400s.\NTherefore, the best a skeptic can do is say
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.36,1:41:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't believe in faith,\Nthey don't believe in miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.36,1:41:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't believe in saints.\NBecause within the linear domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.55,1:41:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that is not their experience.\NSo they're being honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.77,1:41:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of what in the book we call lower mind.\NThe lower mind is very pedestrian,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.77,1:41:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,literal, concrete.\NIt doesn't get the abstract.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.77,1:41:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't get significance.\NIt doesn't get meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.77,1:41:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because those are non-linear.\NLike love is non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.77,1:41:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you prove that love exists?\NYou can't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.77,1:41:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If something brings you delight,\Ncan you prove delight?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.77,1:41:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NSo although the skeptic sensibly lives in that,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.77,1:41:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he does it because he gets enjoyment out of it.\NWhy does he get enjoyment?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.77,1:41:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's non-linear.\NThat's the payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.77,1:41:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He denies the existence of the very purpose\Nfor which he's writing the book in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.77,1:41:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's beyond all that.\NTranquil, non-temporality, beyond proof.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.12,1:42:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is provable is not the highest spiritual truth.\NThat which is confirmable, we confirm it,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.16,1:42:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but we don't prove anything.\NIt's mystical in that the source originates from within.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.16,1:42:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Religiosity is a matter of study of that which is without,\Nand then the attempt to make it also within.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.35,1:42:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ineffable, not capable of definition.\NThe states that I describe experientially,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.76,1:42:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,which began in early childhood\Nand recurred throughout life,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.08,1:42:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,are ineffable.\NThey can't really be described in ordinary,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.08,1:42:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's outside of ordinary human experience.\NThat's why it's called mystical.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.98,1:42:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Simplistic, affirmative.\NTruth does not do anything or cause anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.59,1:42:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth attracts.\NWe try to attract rather than proselytize.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.68,1:43:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not sentimental.\NEmotionality is of a different domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.68,1:43:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionality is an outpouring of animal emotionality.\NIt's non-authoritarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.09,1:43:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no rules or dictates.\NHowever, it stems from certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.80,1:43:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainty is different than authoritarian.\NIt stems from an inner certainty of knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.56,1:43:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes beyond logic or reason,\Njust as the awareness,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.32,1:43:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which came forth periodically in life,\Njust as the awareness that the self is reborn every instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.66,1:43:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to Susie,\NWow, wow, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.48,1:43:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, Fantastic.\NI said,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.92,1:44:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,See, if you thought that up,\Nyou couldn't do that about it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.37,1:44:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because it would be vanity.\NNo, when it comes from without,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.60,1:44:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be ecstatic about it because it's a gift.\NIt just comes out of a yin positionality, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.72,1:44:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The being open to the revelation, you know.\NNon-authoritarian, but certain.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.40,1:44:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, freestanding on its own,\Nself-supporting and natural,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.23,1:44:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,devoid of altered states of consciousness.\NAnd I am not an enthusiast
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.23,1:44:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for manipulating kundalini energy\Nby
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.23,1:44:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,breathing techniques,\Npostures,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.26,1:44:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or any other grotesque distortions\Nof normal human behavior.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.26,1:44:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because it's insurious.\NSee,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.00,1:44:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when your consciousness level is at a certain point,\Nthe kundalini energy flows to that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.32,1:44:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you have become.\NIt automatically summons it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.32,1:45:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you try to force it ahead of time,\Nthen you end up
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.32,1:45:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with difficulties,\Nreligious psychosis,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.32,1:45:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and various things.\NI can remember a guy sitting on the floor telling me,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.32,1:45:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's Jesus Christ, you know.\NI mean, he just overdid it, is all.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.75,1:45:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He did, yeah, he overdid it, yeah.\NNon-predictive, non-sentimental,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.09,1:45:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,non-authoritarian, non-egoistic.\NIt's freestanding,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.22,1:45:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's not artificially induced.\NIt doesn't mean that health,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.22,1:45:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,things that support health, you know,\Na healthy body and a healthy mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.22,1:45:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the Latin phrase.\NWhat's the Latin phrase?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.80,1:45:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Incendio, incendio, Santa.\NOkay, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.80,1:45:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Healthy mind and healthy body, yeah.\NBecause of the experience of the joy of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.99,1:46:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you then enjoy the physicality of the body.\NAnd then the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.08,1:46:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the end of it, 38?\NOkay, now spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.72,1:46:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, there's 144 of them.\N144, plus I jotted down another 20 or so.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.72,1:46:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no shortage of spiritual truth out there.\NThese have all been calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.71,1:46:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all, I guess they meet all the criteria.\NThey meet all the criteria,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.71,1:46:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best of our understanding.\NAnd we've drawn them from a number of different
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.84,1:46:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,religious backgrounds, spiritual backgrounds,\Ndifferent eras.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.25,1:46:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The first enlightenment,\Nreally enlightened sages,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.41,1:46:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,emerged in the Aryan pre-India\Nof about 5000 BC.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.41,1:46:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,About 5000 BC,\Nthe great sages began to appear
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.99,1:47:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in ancient India.\NAll right, so here's 144.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.93,1:47:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They all calibrate extremely well.\NThey've all withstood the test of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.93,1:47:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll go back,\Nstarting with the previous list,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.93,1:47:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we've got some more, too.\NA lot of catalogs that popularize spiritual books,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.83,1:47:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,they tend to be a little overly slick to me.\NAnd most of them are over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.83,1:47:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We recently, we got one yesterday,\Nthe day before.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.08,1:47:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone in the catalog, thank God,\Nwas over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.08,1:47:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of them were the 200s, 300s,\Noccasionally 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.08,1:47:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And one or two at 500.\NAnd these are descriptions of spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.82,1:47:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you start with,\Nstart with spiritual learning?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.85,1:48:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You start by inspiration,\Nand you get attracted to reading certain books.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.85,1:48:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to accumulate spiritual knowledge,\Nwhich will later become experiential.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.85,1:48:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of these levels is not better than another.\NSo the first illusion we want to remove
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.46,1:48:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is that a higher number means better than.\NA higher number doesn't mean better than.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.77,1:48:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody who calibrates at 700\Nmakes no sense at all to the audience,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.77,1:48:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and they all walk away,\Nand what the hell was that about?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.93,1:48:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody at 250 who can give you a practical technique\Nthat changes your life
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.03,1:48:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is far more valuable.\NSo each level then
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.03,1:48:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,describes the truth of that level.\NThat's the truth of this level here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.06,1:48:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the truth of this level here\Nis not the same as the truth of this level here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.51,1:48:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo each level then
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.73,1:49:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,denotes a level of conscious awareness.\NNot better than.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.00,1:49:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody with a consciousness level of 210\Nwho starts reading the Dhammapada
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.03,1:49:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't going to make any sense out of it all.\NDoesn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.44,1:49:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's intellectually interesting,\Nbut not really useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.57,1:49:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to\Nstart with humility
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.57,1:49:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and say,\Nyou know what I should do
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.57,1:49:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is go back to the basics\Nand see have I got that.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.57,1:49:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I got the willingness\Nto forgive everything and everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.50,1:49:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time no matter what.\NThere we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.12,1:49:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I got step number one\Nbefore I'm reaching for step number 32.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.53,1:49:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to forgive yourself,\Nforgive mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.92,1:50:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive everything\Nthat you hear and see on the media
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.92,1:50:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and see it all as a panorama.\NThis is all projection and perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.92,1:50:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The projections of the ego\Nand therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.17,1:50:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we have such spiritual advantages\Nin today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.64,1:50:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In times past you could spend your whole life\Njust being a sheep herder
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.64,1:50:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in a small little community\Nand not know more than a few dozen people.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.64,1:50:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can sit in front of your television set.\NThe entire panorama of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.99,1:50:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is projected for your view.\NYou can experience more
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.34,1:50:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and have more life decisions\Nin a couple of minutes
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.52,1:50:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,than you could in a lifetime.\NHow many options do you have
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.52,1:50:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as a sheep herder in a small village\Nin the middle of nowhere?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.75,1:50:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Very few options.\NAnd now you can turn on
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.23,1:50:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and there you've got a million options,\Nperceptions, projections
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.23,1:51:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of value, of goodness, of badness,\Nof evil, of desirability.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.23,1:51:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego has a major workshop now\Nfor free.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.23,1:51:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called TV.\NA great gift because it speeds up time.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:13.80,1:51:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make a thousand decisions,\Na thousand observations
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.80,1:51:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would have taken you a thousand lifetimes.\NAll right, so the first thing to understand
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.54,1:51:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that each level is\Ndescribing a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.76,1:51:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like depths below the sea.\NCertain fish live at certain depths
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.76,1:51:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and a different kind of fish live here\Nand a different kind of fish here.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.76,1:51:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the grouper lives down here.\NThe grouper doesn't live up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.76,1:51:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're looking on this level\Nfor grouperism, you won't find any
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.89,1:51:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't group up there.\NA grouper is a big, monstrous fish
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.99,1:51:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and he eats whole lobsters.\NLook at you doing all those good lobsters,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.99,1:51:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,eating up the good lobsters.\NOne grouper will eat up a thousand dollars
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.99,1:52:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,worth of lobsters in a week.\NWe need fewer groupers
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.95,1:52:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and more lobsters, right?\NYou see how you project the value.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.36,1:52:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, a lobster is worth more\Nthan a grouper.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.36,1:52:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not so.\NLobsterism.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:19.05,1:52:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Grouperism.\NWell, we can go to battle.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.56,1:52:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the lobsters?\NAnd those are the groupers.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.26,1:52:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will kill each other\Nbecause grouper people are evil
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.26,1:52:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and lobster people are good\Nor vice versa.
